cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-54_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-55_ pf-heading-1-h3">Developing children’s healthcare service policies and procedures</h3><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-57_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Below are the critical areas for developing comprehensive policies and procedures essential for children's healthcare services, ensuring their safety, well-being, and effective care.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3">Safeguarding children</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-61_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-62_ pf-text-1">Policies and procedures should include robust safeguarding measures to protect children from abuse, neglect, and exploitation.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-64_ pf-text-1">This includes procedures for identifying and reporting safeguarding concerns, conducting risk assessments, and implementing safeguarding plans.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-66_ pf-heading-1-h3">Consent and capacity</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-68_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-69_ pf-text-1">Clear guidelines should be in place for obtaining informed consent from children and their parents or guardians for medical treatment or procedures.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-71_ pf-text-1">Procedures should outline the process for assessing a child's capacity to consent and respecting their rights to make decisions about their healthcare.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-73_ pf-heading-1-h3">Infection control</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-75_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-76_ pf-text-1">Policies should address infection prevention and control measures specific to children's healthcare settings, including hand hygiene, personal protective equipment (PPE) use, and environmental cleaning.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-78_ pf-text-1">Procedures should detail protocols for managing infectious diseases, outbreak control, and immunisation programs for children.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-80_ pf-heading-1-h3">Medication management</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-82_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-83_ pf-text-1">Policies and procedures should ensure safe prescribing, administration, and monitoring of medications for children, considering factors such as age-appropriate dosages and medication reconciliation.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-85_ pf-text-1">This includes procedures for medication storage, handling, and disposal, as well as documentation of medication administration and adverse reactions.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-87_ pf-heading-1-h3">Emergency response</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-89_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-90_ pf-text-1">Comprehensive emergency response policies and procedures are essential for managing medical emergencies involving children, including cardiac arrest, respiratory distress, and trauma.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-92_ pf-text-1">This includes training staff in pediatric life support techniques, establishing clear roles and responsibilities during emergencies, and maintaining emergency equipment and supplies.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-94_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Paediatric_Care_Excellence_ComplyPlus_Accreditation_Solutions_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_482x.jpg?v=1712845498" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Paediatric_Care_Excellence_ComplyPlus_Accreditation_Solutions_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1712845498 1536w" width="1821" height="2731" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, calc(100vw/3)" loading="lazy" alt="Ensuring Paediatric Safety: ComplyPlus™ Healthcare Standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Ensuring Paediatric Safety: ComplyPlus™ Healthcare Standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-95_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-96_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Wavebreakmedia

